Mix next 5 ingredients with bread crumbs.
Pat mixture into hollow loaf.
Add top of loaf; spread with butter.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in crock-pot and cook on low overnight (or all day).
Great with hamburgers!
Yields 10 servings.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Fill bottom of cookie sheet with solid crackers.
Over slow heat bring margarine and sugar to boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour syrup over crackers and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: wine ciamelle cookies
directions: Place all the liquids together and all the dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Mix the two mixtures together and work into a soft dough.
Roll out into a long rope and cut sections to form a ring.
Dip each circle in milk and then sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 - 375° for about 15 minutes. Watch for light color.

title: homemade waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs, in a large bowl. Separate egg whites into a small bowl and use mixer to whip egg whites to fluffy stage.
Combine egg yolks with dry ingredients in large bowl.
Using mixer, beat egg yolks and dry ingredients to a batter; fold egg whites lightly into batter.
Spoon batter into waffle iron and cook.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pack into container and place in refrigerator.
Let stand in refrigerator for 10 days.

title: creamy jello delite
directions: *Note:
Butterscotch and chocolate pudding may be substituted.

title: lazy woman's pickles
directions: Pack whole cucumbers into gallon jar.
Add alum, pickling salt and pickling spices.
Cover with apple cider vinegar.
Place lid on jar.
Let stand in a cool, dark place for 3 months (do not refrigerate).
Take cucumbers out and slice.
Sprinkle 6 to 8 cups sugar over cucumbers.
Let stand until sugar melts.
Pack into jars; cover with the syrup and seal.
Do not heat.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Measure sugar and flour in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, mix butter, Crisco, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Bring to a rapid boil and add to flour and sugar.
Then add eggs, buttermilk, baking soda and marshmallows.
Put in buttered pan; bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chippy oatmeal raisin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Beat sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 32 bars.

title: some relish to relish
directions: Put green
beans,
pineapple,
onion
and pimentos in a large bowl.
Beat
together
cup
garlic-flavored
wine vinegar and 3 tablespoons olive oil with salt and dill weed to taste. Pour over the bean mixture and chill overnight.
Great with sandwiches.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Drain beans; chop green pepper.
Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to boil.
Mix drained beans, green pepper and onion.
Pour dressing over them.
Let mixture stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: quick easy roll-ups
directions: Brown hamburger meat and pork sausage together. Drain off excess fat.
Add picante sauce and Velveeta cheese, chopped. Simmer until cheese is melted, constantly stirring it.
Remove off burner. Roll up in soft tortillas. Warm tortillas, if desired.

title: italian delight
directions: Brown ground beef and season with garlic salt, black pepper, and a dash of italian spice.
Drain excess fat.
Saute bell pepper and onions in a little margarine until tender.
Add all ingredients except noodles and cheese.
Mix well and set aside.
Cook noodles and add to meat mixture.
Mix well and add into large casserole pan.
Cover top with grated cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees in oven.

title: lite bites
directions: Spread soft cream cheese evenly on each tortilla.
Layer remaining ingredients as follows:
lettuce, onions, tomatoes, 1 slice each of turkey, ham and cheese.
Roll tightly and cut into 1-inch pinwheels.
Arrange on serving plate, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: "the" dip
directions: Mix together the cans of dip, mayonnaise, sour cream, onions and taco seasoning.
Spread mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer tomatoes, then the olives and then the cheese on top.
Serve with plain tortilla chips.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: In a blender, put all ingredients, except ice.
Cover and process.
While mixture is blending, remove feeder cap and add ice.
Blend until smooth.
Yields 4 cups.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes and make juice.
Mix all ingredients and cook 1 hour.
Yield: 22 pints or 11 quarts.

title: candied yams
directions: Bake sweet potatoes and cool.
Peel and slice, place in casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil. Pour over potatoes and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: simple broiled fish
directions: Wash and dry fish.
Place fish in single layer in foil lined shallow baking pan.
Brush with butter and seasonings.
Broil 4 inches from heat source for 5 to 8 minutes per side until fish is browned and flakes when tested with fork.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; reserve juice from the pineapple.
Add this juice to the vanilla pudding and Tang.
Add fruit cocktail, pineapple and bananas.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Chop corned beef into small pieces.
Beat cream cheese and onion dip until smooth.
Fold in corned beef.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Serve with your favorite crackers.
Makes enough for a party.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
1 (20 oz.) package refrigerated sugar cookies.
Press onto greased pizza pan or 15 X 10 baking pan.
Using floured fingers, press dough evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.

title: zucchini and mushroom casserole
directions: Simmer until tender, zucchini, dill and garlic; drain and save 3 tablespoons liquid.
Saute mushrooms and butter.
Add 2 tablespoons flour and 1 cup sour cream; heat slowly.
Put both mixtures in casserole; top with buttered breadcrumbs.
Boil until brown.

title: zucchini-broccoli bake
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add vegetables; cook until tender.
Beat egg slightly; stir in Swiss cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Place vegetables in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour egg mixture over vegetables.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Press vanilla wafer crumbs in pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips, coconut, pecans and milk over crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: sloppy joes(quick and easy)
directions: Brown ground beef and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer a few minutes before serving.

title: meat sauce
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet; drain off fat.
Add onion, garlic and spices.
Cook until onions are translucent.
Add tomatoes and paste; simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add water if needed and adjust seasoning to your taste.
Serve over cooked pasta.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan and chopped parsley.

title: oklahoma potatoes
directions: Mix together thawed potatoes, onion, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and salt.
Layer in greased 13 x 9-inch pan with corn flake crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes covered and uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Crumble beef into a microwave-safe colander.
Place colander in a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with wax paper; microwave at High for 5 to 6 minutes or until the meat is no longer pink, stirring after 3 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, milk, peanut butter and cream cheese.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour in pie shells and freeze.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Crumble the bacon into shell. Cover with the cheese. Beat eggs, milk and salt and pepper. Pour into shell. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together oats, sugar, butter and flour. Fold in egg whites until well blended. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Cool. Makes 3 dozen.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Cream brown sugar and Crisco.
Add egg and mix well.
Combine applesauce and soda; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in salt and spices; add flour and mix thoroughly.
Fill greased pans or baking cups half full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: lasagna a la popeye
directions: Preheat skillet and saute onion and garlic until golden. Next, add sweet sausage and cook until meat is done.
Drain off grease.
To Ricotta cheese, add egg, parsley, basil and Romano cheese; whip until incorporated.

title: indian cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients except cheese and bacon drippings.
Pour half of bacon drippings in mixture and the other half in skillet.
Pour half of mixture in skillet, then sprinkle with cheese.
Add rest of mixture, then top with remaining cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 45 minutes.
Let set 30 minutes before serving.

title: hot florentine dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave cream cheese in 2-quart casserole at High for 30 seconds.

Add seasonings and milk to cheese and cream together. Place package of spinach on plate; microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes, or until defrosted, rotating 1/2 turn after 3 minutes. Drain spinach thoroughly.
Stir ham and spinach into cheese mixture.
Fold in sour cream and pecans.
Microwave at High 4 to 6 minutes, or until very hot, stirring gently after 2 minutes, then every minute.
Place casserole on candle warmer or warming tray and serve with crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: dumplings
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in 2 beaten eggs to flour mixture.
Add enough water to make a biscuit like dough.
Drop in hot broth or gravy and cook covered for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients until creamy.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda into mixture and mix well.
Add chips and pecans, if desired.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add taco sauce and a little water and simmer. Drain grease.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown onion with ground beef.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Add 3 paste cans water.
Add spices and chopped garlic; simmer 40 minutes.
Stir in instant rice; let sit 5 minutes without heat. Spoon over corn chips; top with lettuce, tomatoes, avocados and cheese.
Add taco sauce as desired.

title: california cole slaw
directions: Blend soup mix with sour cream.
Add other ingredients.

title: bie-rocks or beuroc
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Remove from pan.
In butter (if needed) cook cabbage until wilted.
Add hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cool.
Roll dough into 9-inch square.
Place 3 tablespoons of meat mixture in center.
Fold corners together. Place folded sides down.
Place in a warm place to rise.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Stash some late summer fruits in the freezer to enjoy all year.
Just three steps for freezing melons:

title: easy tempura
directions: Chop vegetables into smaller pieces.
Mash drained tofu and then mix in surumi.
Add the egg and chopped vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drop by tablespoon into a heated frying pan with vegetable oil heated at medium setting.
Cook both sides until each piece is lightly brown.

title: rich hot rolls
directions: Scald milk. Add margarine, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast on warm water. Stir to dissolve. Add 1 1/2 cups flour to milk mixture. Beat well by hand or with electric mixer at low speed 1 minute. Beat in eggs and yeast. Gradually stir in enough remaining flour a little at a time to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of bowl. Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth, satiny and no longer sticky, 5 to 8 minutes. Place in lightly greased bowl; invert to grease top. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Punch down and turn onto board. Divide and shape into rolls. Cover with light towel and let rise until doubled. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 30 rolls.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Pick meat off when cool. Cut in bite-size pieces.
Mix dry ingredients.
Make a depression in center.
Add eggs, milk and food coloring.
Mix until bowl is clean.
Dough will be stiff.
Roll dough out, cut into noodles, drop in chicken broth and cook until done.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: friendship cake(30 day process)
directions: Combine starter (if available from a friend), sugar and peaches (halved with juice).
Mix well and put in 1 gallon glass or crock jar with lid.
Cover and set on counter; stir daily for 10 days, then add 2 1/2 cups sugar and crushed pineapple and juice.
Stir well for 10 days, covered.
Add fruit cocktail and juice and 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir well for 10 days, covered.
Add maraschino cherries with juice and 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir well 10 days, covered.
At end of 30 days, strain.
Divide fruit into 4 portions and juice into 1 1/2 cups portions.
Keep 1 for yourself.
Next time, give friends each of 1 1/2 cups juice and their recipe.

title: special occasion punch
directions: Chill pineapple juice and soda.
Just as party begins, mix chilled juice and soda with coconut cream and add ice cream or sherbet and serve.

title: odorless tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: garlic-parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, cheese and garlic powder in a shallow dish.
Melt margarine in a shallow dish.
Dip each chicken breast in the margarine, then coat with crumb mixture.
Place on lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on thickness of chicken.

title: crab stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Brush mushroom caps with butter and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and fill caps.
Place on baking pan, filled side up.
Broil 6 inches from heat about 5 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and mushrooms are heated through.

title: microwave zucchini casserole
directions: Bake zucchini and onion in a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch microwave dish covered with plastic wrap; turn back corner to vent. Microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; cover with paper towel and microwave on Medium-high for 8 to 10 minutes. Stir after 3 to 4 minutes.

title: deviled sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts in boiling water until tender-crisp (5 to 7 minutes).
Drain.
Melt butter in skillet; add onion, mustard and thyme.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add bread crumbs, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 1 more minute.
Add this mixture to the drained Brussels sprouts.
Shake/stir to cover the sprouts with the seasoned mixture.
Cook until desired doneness.

title: praline cookies
directions: Arrange graham	crackers
on 13 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan. Bring
brown
sugar
and butter to a boil; boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Add
nuts;
mix together and pour over graham crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cut into squares while warm.

title: peach pickle
directions: Put spices in bag and mix.
Then mix everything, except peaches, and boil for 20 minutes.
Peel peaches and put in boiling mixture slowly.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: baked fruit
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place pineapple slices and peach halves, pit side up.
Drop a pat of margarine in each peach half. Sprinkle brown sugar and curry powder on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Crush 1 tube Ritz crackers and combine with 1 stick melted butter.
Spread over potato mixture; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green beans pennsylvania dutch
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crispy.
Remove bacon and crumble. Drain off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add onions and brown lightly.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and dry mustard.
Cook green beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir reserved liquid in skillet. Cook, stirring until mixture boils.
Blend in brown sugar and vinegar.
Add green beans and heat thoroughly.
Turn into serving dish and garnish with egg and crumbled bacon.
Serves 4.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In large pan cook onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Combine in a bowl with chicken and green chilies; set aside.
In same pan, melt 3 tablespoons margarine. Blend in flour, cumin and salt.
Stir in chicken broth at once. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat, stir in sour cream and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Stir 1/2 cup sauce into chicken.
Dip each tortilla into sauce to soften, fill with 1/4 cup of chicken mix.
Roll up.
Arrange rolls in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pour remaining sauce over all.
Sprinkle remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: green bean stew
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil. Cut beans in half. Add to onion and garlic. Cover and let steam for 30 minutes, stirring frequently. Add water and tomatoes until even with beans. Add seasonings to taste. Cook 15 minutes or until tender.

title: lucky seven stir-fry
directions: Combine meat, cornstarch and soy sauce; let stand 10 minutes. Stir-fry meat in 2 tablespoons hot oil in wok or large skillet over high heat 2 minutes; remove.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in same pan.
Add vegetables; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Combine Lucky Seven Stir-Fry Sauce and red pepper; pour mixture over vegetables. Cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens.
Stir in meat to combine.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and onion juice; blend thoroughly.
Add oil slowly, beating constantly and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seeds and beat until well mixed.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch skillet.
Add brown sugar.
Stir until just melted.
Pour over pineapple cubes that have been arranged in bottom of square pan.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder 3 times. Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat sugar in gradually.
Fold in lemon juice, 1/3 cup reserved pineapple juice and dry ingredients, alternately.
Mix only enough to blend.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until golden brown.
Let set 5 minutes and flip over onto serving plate or cardboard lined with paper.

title: chili bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for cookouts!

title: fried turkey
directions: Thaw turkey.
Mix all ingredients and thoroughly cover the turkey on all sides.
Refrigerate.
Fry in a deep pot at 300° for 4 minutes per pound.

title: sesame cucumber salad
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a small saucepan.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Cool completely.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
Mix and take off heat.
Add cocoa. Heat milk in another pan.
Add milk to other mixture.
Add sugar and boil.
Stir until thickened.
Serve over ice cream.

title: opossum pie
directions: Blend the flour or graham cracker crumbs, oleo and chopped nuts (optional).
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: zucchini cake
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs until fluffy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla until it is thick and lemon colored.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Invert on racks and let cool completely.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Top each pork chop with a slice of onion and a green pepper ring. Cover with cooked rice.
Top with a can of tomato soup.
Spread evenly over the rice.
Cover tightly and bake for 1 hour at 350°. May want to uncover the last 10 to 15 minutes.

title: low-fat applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Blend all dry ingredients (except soda) and fruit.
Heat applesauce.
Add soda to it, then alternate a little at a time to sugar and shortening.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can use Bundt pan or loaf.

title: raised donuts
directions: Combine yeast, sugar and water.
Let stand until it bubbles. Scald milk; stir in shortening.
Let cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Turn out onto floured board and knead will.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with donut cutter or glass.
Fry in hot grease until golden brown; sprinkle with sugar.

title: chicken or seafood aspic salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the hot water and let cool.
Mix all ingredients and pour in glass 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cool and let harden.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix ingredients together in order given.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan until barely warm.
Ice cake with following recipe.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine and sugar in a medium bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place dough in cookie press.
Form desired shapes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 9 minutes, or until set (not brown).
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: barbara bruu's sourdough bread and starter
directions: Combine Sourdough Starter, sugar, salt, oil and warm water in large mixing bowl.
Using heavy-duty mixer and dough hooks, gradually mix in all the bread flour.
Place dough in large oiled bowl, brushing oil over top to keep from drying out.
Cover with clean dish towel and let rise all day or overnight.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, peppers and celery in margarine until tender, not brown.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp last and simmer until shrimp are tender.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and vanilla. Work in flour, salt and nuts until the dough holds together.
Shape the dough into 1-inch balls and place them on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set but not brown.
While warm, roll in 10x sugar.
Cool and roll in sugar again.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt butter and stir in flour. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet sour slaw
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar until sugar is melted.
Add salt and mayonnaise.
Mix with cabbage.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef loose with diced onion.
Cool after draining fat.
Chop lettuce, tomato and green pepper into small pieces. Mix in large bowl with cooked, cooled meat.
Add Catalina dressing, crush Doritos in bag and mix 3/4 of bag in salad.
Toss and add remaining Doritos on top.

title: aunt june's sky-high biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and cream of tartar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add egg and milk, stirring quickly and briefly.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll or pat gently to 1-inch thickness. Cut into 1 to 2-inch biscuits.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Toss cabbage and carrots together in a large mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise and sweet pickle juice. Blend together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: methodist cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding into fruit.
Mix Tang into pineapple juice and pour over the mixture.

title: spanish bar cake
directions: Put apple pie mix into blender with eggs, apple pie spice and cloves.
Blend until smooth.
Dump into 2-quart mixing bowl and beat in cake mix with electric mixer on medium speed, blending thoroughly.
Remove beaters.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.
Frost.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine butter and crumbs and press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat eggs, sugar and butter for no less than 15 minutes; pour into crust.
Top with bananas and pineapple.
Spread on Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: cranberry-pear crisp
directions: Peel, core and thinly slice pears or apples.
(You may use two of each if available.)
Wash and pick over cranberries.
Toss pears and berries in a bowl with sugar and cinnamon.
Spread on bottom of 10-inch pie dish or other flat baking dish.
Combine flour, brown sugar, rolled oats and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spread evenly over cranberry mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.
Serve plain or with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: fruit salad(working family recipe)
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Serve.

title: german farmers breakfast
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Crumble into small pieces.
Add green pepper, onion, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, about 5 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown.
Break eggs over potato mixture and cook until eggs are set.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole mix sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Microwave for 3 to 5 minutes on High until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla; stir well. Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes more.
Add soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto greased sheet.
Let cool for 1 hour.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: grandma pierson's easy pudding cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients together in mixing bowl until mixed thoroughly.
Roll balls of dough (the size of walnuts) until smooth.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten tops of balls with the bottom of a glass.
Decorate with pecans, sprinkles, colored sugar, Hershey's Kisses, etc.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned on bottom.
Cookies should be soft. Place on wax paper to cool.
Yield:
12 to 20 cookies.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and the rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° until custard is firm, approximately 45 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Leave chicken breasts whole or cut in strips.
Cook chicken in large nonstick frying pan.
Add dressing when chicken is 3/4 of the way cooked; reduce heat until done.
Serve with rice or mixed vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Mix noodles, diced chicken, soup, sour cream, mixed vegetables, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in casserole dish and cover top of casserole with thin biscuit layers.
Pour melted margarine over top of casserole and bake at 400° until biscuits are brown (about 15 minutes).

title: pizza cookie
directions: Press cookie dough in a pizza pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Beat cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together.
Spread cream mixture on cookie.
Top with fruit or nuts.
Suggestions: Bananas, grapes, strawberries, kiwi and pineapple.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together baking soda, vanilla and salt; set aside.
Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a soft ball in water.
Add raw peanuts; cook until it reaches hard crack on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add soda mixture and mix well. Pour up while foaming into greased jellyroll pans and spread thin. Let cool and break into pieces.

title: candied pecans
directions: Mix ingredients and bake on cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° in a greased pie dish for 45 minutes.
Springtime fresh!

title: spinach rarebit casserole
directions: Partially cook spinach and drain.
Thaw rarebit on top of double boiler.
Place
1/3 rarebit in bottom of casserole.
Add spinach, bacon and water chestnuts.
Top with remaining rarebit. Sprinkle with French fried onions.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes in rectangular casserole.
Serves 8 generously.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook hamburger until no longer pink.
Drain.
Add kidney beans and sauce.
Add chili to taste.
Serve with cornbread.

title: tomato soup spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sift flour with soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at high speed, cream 1 cup butter until light.
Gradually beat in brown sugar until light.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Combine soup with enough water to measure 2 cups.
Mix well.
At low speed, add flour (in fourths) to sugar mixture alternately with soup mixture (in thirds), beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat just until combined.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 30 minutes.
Turn out of pan and let cool completely on rack.
Frost top with cream cheese frosting.
Cut into squares.
Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Spread in greased and floured cookie sheet.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on dish towel sprinkled with powdered sugar. Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together.
Cool. Unroll and fill.

title: quick and easy donuts
directions: Roll out biscuits and cut hole in the middle.
Place oil in deep fryer or frying pan.
Fry until brown; take out.
Drain; sprinkle with powdered sugar or frosting of your choice.

title: "corny" corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased pan at 450° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: buffet cheese eggs
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with flour tortillas, cut to fit (can overlap).
Sprinkle with 1/2 of chilies, 1/2 of ham and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese. In medium bowl, combine eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over layered ingredients.
Decorate with strips of pepper on top.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until puffed and bubbly.
Cool 5 minutes and cut in squares.

title: ida duff's orange marmalade
directions: Removes seeds of lemons and oranges; chop in food processor. Mix together.
Add pineapple, sugar and water.
Stir to dissolve sugar. Slowly bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Boil for 1/2 hour after mixture starts to boil and not more than 3/4 hour at the most.
Pour into sterilized jelly glasses and cover with paraffin.
Makes 8 jelly glasses.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and then add eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Add baking soda to water and stir. Alternately add dry ingredients and liquid ingredients, soda water, vanilla and buttermilk until well mixed.
Drop by heaping teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes in center of oven.

title: jane's potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for 2 hours.
Mix first 6 ingredients together. Add Cheddar cheese and sour cream and mix.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan; top with cornflakes and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
May add chunks of ham for a main-dish casserole.

title: braised red cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in half.
Wash and drain, then core and shred. Melt margarine in a heavy type kettle on low heat.
Add shredded cabbage and saute for five minutes.
Add sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Toss until mixed.
Cook 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli tortellini salad
directions: Cook Tortellini to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain. Rinse with cold water.

title: cherry vanilla fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cream, milk, corn syrup and butter in large heavy saucepan or skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally until candy thermometer reaches 238° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat and cool (100°).
Add vanilla. Beat briskly until fudge thickens and begins to lose its gloss. Stir in cherries.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares when firm.
This fudge is pretty to serve at Christmastime.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: sweet-sour pork roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour.
Pour off fat.
Combine tomato sauce, lemon juice, water, rind, 1/2 teaspoon salt, brown sugar and nutmeg in saucepan. Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Add juice to mixture; simmer 10 minutes.
Add pineapple and raisins.
Pour over roast.
Roast until done, about 2 hours.

title: lime cheese salad
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to jello.
Stir in crushed pineapple and let stand until partly congealed.
Then prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Stir Dream Whip and grated cheese into the congealed mixture.
Chill.

title: hot wieners
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti supreme
directions: Lightly brown hamburger, onions and green pepper in shortening.
Stir occasionally.
Add and heat rest of ingredients, except for 1/2 cup cheese, including cooked spaghetti.
Mix well. Place in casserole dish and top with 1/2 cup sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal molasses bread
directions: Bring water to a boil and add to rolled oats.
Mix in oil, molasses, salt and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast solution and eggs, stir altogether.
Add flour.
Mix and knead until waxy.
Cover. When double in bulk, punch down and rise again (not necessary, but makes better bread).
Shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise again in bread pans until slight indentation shows.
Bake about 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
After 20 minutes, cover with foil to keep from browning too much.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Roll nuts in flour then mix all together.
Line pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pastry shell. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: beef and cheddar goulash
directions: Brown beef in butter or margarine.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Simmer mixture 5 minutes.
Add noodles and green beans; toss lightly, but well.
Pour into greased shallow baking pan; sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: glorified chicken
directions: In skillet, using medium heat, cook chicken until brown on all sides.
Remove from heat and drain off fat.
Stir in soup, black pepper, thyme and milk.
Return to low heat, cover and simmer 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over toast or rice.
Serves 4.

title: microwave orange glazed chicken for two
directions: Split chicken breast; rinse and pat dry.
Place chicken in 9-inch round microproof baking dish, thick edges toward rim. Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Pour off fat and set aside.

title: banana split
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine.
Pat evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, 2 sticks softened margarine, eggs and vanilla for 15 minutes.
Spread on crust. Slice bananas long way.
Top with pineapple, Cool Whip, nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: corn fingers
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a 425° oven.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and mix until blended.
Knead 6 to 8 times.
Roll into strips 3 x 3-inches and roll in margarine. Arrange in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until well browned. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg. Add oil and applesauce. Sift in dry ingredients. Mix well. Add walnuts and cherries. Pour batter into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes. Yields 15 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring Karo syrup and sugar to a boil at medium heat for 1 minute.
Add peanuts.
Cook 25 minutes at slow boil.
Mix salt and soda on waxed paper.
Pour in and stir fast.
Place tinfoil on cookie sheet and grease.
Pour candy on foil and cool.
Break candy into pieces.

title: quick lunch
directions: Cook steak in a little fat until done; do not season.
Reduce heat.
When meat is done, pour the can of mushroom soup over the meat.
Stir.
Serve hot on buttered toast.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Melt butter and mix with bread cubes.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Combine other ingredients; stir in water.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with reserved bread cubes.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef. Drain. Add all 4 cans of soup and heat. Place chips in bottom of a large casserole dish. Pour meat and soup mixture over it and top with grated cheese. Bake for 5 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat whipping cream in a chilled bowl until stiff.
Beat eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy; fold into whipped cream.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Fold into mixture.

title: apricot mochi
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover tightly with tinfoil and bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and after 15 minutes, remove tinfoil.
Cool for several hours; cut into bite size pieces and roll in potato starch or kinako (soybean flour).
Shake off excess starch.
Makes 48 servings.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Fold in remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 mixture into oblong dish and let set. Spread top with sour cream.
Add remaining mixture.
Place in refrigerator until time to serve.
Yields 12 servings.

title: enchilada
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and drain off oil.
Add flour, chili powder, cumin, salt and garlic.
Mix well; add water and cook on low heat until thickened.
You will need to taste it to make sure you will not need anymore chili powder.
It needs to have a taco seasoning taste.

title: inside out chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 12-cup tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed with finger.
Do not overbake. Cool 15 minutes in pan, remove and continue cooling on rack.
When cool dust with confectioners sugar.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In bowl, beat eggs, butter and milk together. In a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish, layer bread cubes, half of cheese, sausage and mushrooms. Pour egg mixture over all and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes. For glass dish, bake at 325°. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chocolate chews(diabetic)
directions: Blend first six ingredients with fork.
Round into balls. Roll in nuts.
Freeze.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cook sugar, flour, milk and egg together until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Slice strawberries and cover with sugar. Crush vanilla wafers.
Put vanilla wafers in bottom of dish. Cover with pudding.
Add sweetened strawberries on top of pudding. Sprinkle some strawberries on top of pudding.
Sprinkle some more vanilla wafers on top of that.
Also pecans.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle some more vanilla wafer crumbs and pecans.
This is good frozen.
Cut in squares and serve.
Needs to be set out of freezer ahead of time.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Drain.
Add milk, soup, corned beef, green peppers, onion and cheese.
Mix together and pour into casserole.
Cover with potato chips or chow mein noodles.
Bake.

title: hummus party dip
directions: In a blender or food processor fitted with the metal blade, combine 1/4 cup bean liquid and remaining ingredients.
Process until mixture is smooth paste.
Add more liquid if needed to make desired consistency.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with crackers or pita bread.
Use as a dip for crudites or use as a stuffing for celery.
Makes 1 cup.

title: south-of-the-border cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Set aside. Cream margarine and instant coffee. Cut orange into thin strips, add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Gradually add sugar, beat well after each addition.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Add part of flour mixture, part of orange and molasses; beat well.
Add remaining flour mixture, orange juice and molasses.
Beat well. Pour into waxed paper-lined pan, 10 x 5 x 13-inches.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sour cream yeast rolls
directions: Combine oleo, sour cream, sugar and salt and cook over low heat until oleo melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir into above mixture.
Add flour.
Stir.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Punch down and divide in half.
Roll into 12-inch circle.
Cut each circle into 12 wedges.
Roll each wedge into jelly roll fashion, starting at wide end.
Place on greased sheet.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix and chill before serving, about 4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: ice cream
directions: Scald milk and remove from heat.
Fold in six beaten egg yolks, then add vanilla and condensed milk.
(This may be prepared ahead of time and put in refrigerator until ready to use.)
Fold in six beaten egg whites and finish filling freezer with milk.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in covered container.

title: manwich casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually. Beat in eggs; add bananas. Beat well. Add flour sifted with soda & salt. Add walnuts. Bake 50-60 minutes in greased bread tin at 350°.

title: peachy cream dessert
directions: In a bowl, cut butter into the flour until crumbly. Stir in the pecans. Press into a 13 x 9 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.

title: sunshine golden yellow cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add 3/4 cup milk and Crisco. Beat vigorously by hand or at medium speed for 2 minutes. Add eggs, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2 or two 9-inch round greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chow-chow
directions: Cook vinegar, sugar and spices 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 30 minutes.
Put in hot, clean jars and seal.

title: sophie's rice pudding
directions: Bring milk and water to a boil.
Add pinch of salt, then lower flame to a simmer.
Add rice.
Let it simmer until all liquid is almost absorbed.
Remove pot from flame.
Add vanilla and drop of yellow food coloring.
Stir in cup of sugar.
Cook 1 hour or more when dissolved.
Pour into bowl.
Add a sprinkle of cinnamon. Chill.

title: mincemeat squares
directions: Cook mincemeat in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Cream shortening; add sugar.
Gradually beat in molasses; add dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread half the oatmeal mixture over greased shallow pan (9 x 9-inches).
Press mixture down firmly. Spread mincemeat filling over oatmeal mixture.
Spread remaining half of oatmeal mixture over mincemeat.
Press down firmly with fingers.
Bake for 30
minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and cut in squares.
Makes 16 pieces.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, salt, eggs, pepper, onion and corn flakes together.
Make sauce with ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Heat sauce mixture until hot.
Put half of sauce in the meat mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Pour remaining sauce over meat loaf and bake for 15 minutes.

title: quick chocolate sheath cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and flour together in mixing bowl.
Heat oleo, cocoa and water in saucepan until it reaches boiling point.
Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients and add buttermilk with soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour batter into pan, 11 x 15 x 1-inch.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: bulgogi(korean style marinated thin beef steak)
directions: Mix sauce portions together.
Add meat and stir.
Allow mixture to set in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir-fry in small to medium batches over medium heat.
May be served on roll or a bed of rice.

title: fix-ahead chicken
directions: Brown chicken; place in 2-quart casserole.
Stir soup, milk and seasonings together; add vegetables and cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Pour chicken in casserole.
Cover; can be kept in refrigerator until 1 hour before serving or can be used right away.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: nut crescents
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients and 1 tablespoon water.
Stir in flour and nuts; mix well.
Shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on a rack; roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 60 crescents.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Cook over medium heat, turning occasionally, until brown, for about 20 minutes.

title: mama's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions.
Drain and combine
all
ingredients; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish. Place sliced
cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain canned vegetables and combine with other vegetables. Mix together the vinegar, sugar and oil.
Pour over vegetables and chill several hours.
To serve, drain the juice and save to pour over unused portion.

title: zuni succotash
directions: Brown beef well in oil.
Add vegetables and simmer until meat is tender.
Add sunflower seeds to thicken and salt to taste. Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Place in casserole dish; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir flour and spices together.
Add sugar and oats.
Mix in thoroughly the oil, milk and egg.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes about three dozen.

title: corned beef dinner(from recipes for diabetics)
directions: Cover meat with cold water in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; drain.
Add water to cover; again bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Cook until meat is nearly tender (about 3 hours), skimming off as much fat as possible from cooking water.
(If you remove meat from broth and refrigerate, fat will harden and remove easily.)
Add vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are done (about 15 minutes).
Remove vegetables from water; drain and trim fat from meat.
Makes 16 (3 ounce) servings.
Contains 300 calories per serving.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Blend flour, milk, sugar, baking powder and butter.
Heat fruit and pour into buttered baking dish.
Then pour batter over fruit and bake at 350° until brown.

title: magic bars
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 2 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter evenly.
Sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips over coconut.
Pour milk evenly over top.
Press nuts into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese fritters
directions: Combine the flour and the salt.
Beat the egg with the water and add to the flour.
Beat until the mixture is thick.
Dip the cheese in the batter and fry until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup with rotary beater.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into frozen pie crust shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: no-fat fruit salad
directions: May omit pineapple and use 2 cups orange juice.

title: baked pork chops and dressing
directions: Brown chops on both sides. Mix together bread cubes, poultry seasoning, onion, water and melted butter. Place chops in a baking dish and place a mound of stuffing on each chop. Blend cream of mushroom soup and water. Pour over chops and stuffing. Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 1 1/4 hours.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cooking oil, together.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil and cook until a golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook frozen spinach and onion in 3/4 inch water.
Mix rest of the ingredients with spinach and onions.
Pour into greased casserole and bake in a 350 degree oven for 25-30 minutes until the center is set.

title: london broil
directions: Make marinade of wine, olive oil, garlic, salt, peppercorns, mustard and thyme.
Cut away fat and score meat cross-wise
on both
sides.
In
large container, pour the marinade over
steak. Cover
and
refrigerate
for 2 hours (preferably overnight), turn
occasionally.
Before
cooking, drain
and retain
marinade. Press
peppercorns
into scored steak.
Let stand
30 minutes, season with salt.

title: macaroni by catherine
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Dot with butter and set aside.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Use soup pot. Add water. Bring water to a boil on top of stove, adding all the ingredients except shrimp. Then add shrimp and cook until tender. Drain, reserving fluid. Place shrimp in blender with 2 cups of liquid. Blend until finely chopped. Add to remaining liquid in pot. Serve hot with crackers.

title: easy-does-it donuts
directions: In medium
mixing
bowl,
beat	eggs; set aside.
Drain both cans of
apples
or blueberries from muffin mixes; add to beaten eggs.
Stir
in
flour
and dry muffin mixes.
On well floured pastry
sheet,
roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut out doughnuts with a floured, 2 1/2-inch diameter doughnut cutter, pressing straight down.
Meanwhile, in a large saucepan,
or
deep fat
fryer, heat cooking oil to 375°.
Fry the doughnuts and holes,
a few at a time, for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or	until golden brown, turning several times.
Drain on paper toweling.
If desired,
sprinkle	powdered sugar over tops or roll
in granulated	sugar
or
cinnamon sugar.
Store cooled doughnuts in a sealed container.

title: prairie hot dish
directions: Brown meat and add onion. Mix in salt, pepper, corn, soup, water and cheese.
Spread it in a large cake pan and top with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in meat, oregano and gravy.
Season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat through.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease pan (heat in oven).
Mix all ingredients together and bake 30 minutes or until it is golden brown.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until well blended and smooth. Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.

title: party pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on party rye bread slices. Bake in slow oven (250° to 300°) for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hearty hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onions, drain.
In large pot (at least 8 quarts) mix all ingredients, except salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Check about 30 minutes before serving and add salt and pepper.
If soup is to thick add water to desired consistency.
Soup can be frozen or canned for later use.

title: potato cheese patties
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except oil; mix well. In large skillet, drop mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls, a few at a time, in small amount of hot oil.
Fry until golden on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Take a large size mixing bowl and add ingredients as follows: Line bottom and sides of bowl with lettuce.
Add celery, red onion, green peppers and sweet peas.
Mix Miracle Whip with sour cream.
Smear over top like a frosting.
Let set several hours or overnight.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and Bac*Os or crumbled crisp bacon bits.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 1/4 hours.

title: donna's zucchini moussaka
directions: In large skillet, brown zucchini and onion in oil.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Brown beef; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic, salt and cinnamon.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread over zucchini and onion.
Blend cottage cheese and egg; spread over meat.
Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine cinnamon and sugar. Toss biscuits in mixture a few at a time. Place sugared biscuits on a greased
bunt pan. Combine margarine and remaining sugar mix and pour over biscuits. Bake at 359 degrees for 40 minutes or until brown. Turn onto serving plate. Pull off pieces.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add molasses and eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with hot water. Bake in a greased 9-inch square pan for 50 minutes at 350°.
Good luck!

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and egg.
Add the orange juice and rind alternately with the dry ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and ice.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: texas rice delight
directions: Cook sausage and onions until sausage is golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add sausage and onion mixture to rice and pour into well-greased casserole.
Make a layer of grated cheese. Top with tomatoes to which Tabasco sauce has been added.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken tender in 1 1/2 cups water (save broth).
Cool. Tear into bite size pieces and place in 10 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Cover with cream of chicken soup (undiluted).
Chop celery and onion.
Saute in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Cool. Mix with broth from chicken, beaten egg, sage, salt and pepper. Add this mixture to enough chicken flavored Stove Top stuffing to make desired consistency.
Top casserole with it.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt
margarine
and
pour over brown sugar.
Cream the two. Add
eggs
one
at
a time and beat after each addition. Sift flour and baking powder together and add gradually to the creamed mixture.
Beat
well.
Stir
in
nuts
and
chocolate chips.
Turn into
a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry champagne
directions: Pour all ingredients over crushed ice in punch bowl.
Serve at once.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Fold milk and Cool Whip together.
Add cherries, drained pineapple and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put in freezer. Take out about 15 or 20 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares and serve.
Always a dessert ready for company!

title: russian borsch
directions: Add cabbage and onion to boiling stock.
Meanwhile, cook and puree other vegetables, then add to the soup and cook about 10 minutes more.
Salt to taste.

title: sirloin tips
directions: Slice sirloin steak into thin strips.
Brown in oil.
Add salt and pepper, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce to suit taste. Cover and cook about 10 minutes, or until tender.
Add cut up peppers and onions with water.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes. Serve with baked potatoes and salad.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash sweet potatoes in blender, using 1/3 cup syrup in can. Mix other ingredients in sweet potatoes.
Spread in greased glass dish.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine the first 11 ingredients in a large bowl; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: garden tuna pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl combine the first 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Makes 8 cups.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Beat eggs for 1 minute.
Add brown sugar and mix; add white sugar and mix.
Add melted oleo, then add flour, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Bake 35 minutes.
(When done, insides will be slightly moist.)
Cut when warm.
Store in tight container.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa in a mixing bowl.
Add milk and margarine.
Do not mix.

title: dilly beans
directions: Boil beans 10 to 15 minutes.
Pack in jars and put garlic, pepper an dill seed on top of beans.
Boil vinegar, salt and water and pour over beans.
Wait 15 days before opening.
Makes 6 pints.

title: crumble burgers
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion, green pepper and celery. Simmer until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Serve on buns.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour off pineapple juice and mix with pudding.
Mix in other ingredients.
Place in bowl.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Thaw the potatoes.
Mix all the ingredients.
Take 2 cups corn flakes and mix with 1/4 cup butter.
Put it on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce picnic cake
directions: In large saucepan, heat margarine and applesauce until butter is melted.
Beat eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add with beaten eggs to applesauce mixture.
Add walnuts and put in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald, peel and drain tomatoes.
Cut up or put in blender the peppers and onions. Put in blender. Add some of the vinegar with it so you have some liquid. Mix all together and cook. Slow boil; can't be stirred out.
Cook about 2 hours or until thick.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sugar.
Chill in refrigerator 1 hour.
Spoon into small balls and roll in sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini & hot sausage supper
directions: Cook onions in 2 Tbsp. oil.
Add celery.
Then sausage.
Brown and Drain.
Put in a large pot and add peppers in sauce and roasted peppers, tomatoes with chilies.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes.
Add parmesan cheese and rice.
Cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
You can use Fresh peppers and tomato sauce if you want.
Very good with Italian Bread.

title: jello delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Mash the frozen raspberries into dissolved jello, then put in the vanilla ice cream.
Beat up well.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Put the cream cheese, sugar and cocoa powder in the mixing bowl and stir until well blended.
Roll the mixture into marble size balls in the palms of your hands.
You can make them bigger if you like.
Spread the chocolate sprinkles on the work surface and carefully roll the truffles in them, then put each one in a paper cup.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix together; store in tightly sealed container.
Use approximately 2 teaspoons per cup hot water.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until thick (not too thick).
Stir in Jell-O.
Put whole strawberries in cool pie shell.
Cover with Jell-O mixture.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix together the grated cheese, flour, salt and red pepper. Melt margarine and pour over cheese-flour mixture.
Mix well. Add Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Using hands, roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with fork.
Bake approximately 15 to 20 minutes at 300° or until edges are slightly brown.
Let cool.
Remove carefully with spatula.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in 2 to 2 1/2-quart glass container and stir.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High until mixture boils.
Remove and stir well.
Add 2 cups raw peanuts. Microwave 10 minutes on High. Remove and add butter, vanilla and food coloring.
Stir well until mixture loses gloss, but is still runny.
Spoon by tablespoon onto buttered cookie sheet or wax paper.
Makes 25.

title: brown sugar oatmeal cake
directions: Add boiling water to quick oats; set aside to cool.
Combine margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and oat mixture.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; add to first mixture.

title: tea sandwich
directions: Cut bread crusts off and cut bread into rectangle shapes (3 rectangles per slice).
Smash shrimp with a fork and combine with mayo and dye.
Spread on bread and sprinkle with chives.

title: grilled mushrooms
directions: Thread mushrooms on skewers.
Combine butter, dill and garlic salt; brush over mushrooms.
Grill over hot coals for 10 to 15 minutes, basting and turning every 5 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: crunchy sunflower coleslaw
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons white vinegar.
Sprinkle sunflower seeds and bacon on each serving.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Let margarine and cheese come to room temperature.
Mix well, adding flour, salt and soup mix.
Form into four rolls with circumference the size of a penny.
Wrap each and freeze.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese with butter.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, chives and pimento.
Mix thoroughly. Divide rolls into 4 squares, pressing seams between each 2 triangles together.
Spoon 1/4 chicken mixture onto center of each square.
Pull sides to center to cover chicken.
Brush each square with melted butter.
Sprinkle croutons over squares and bake on a cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan candy
directions: Mix pecans and oleo.
Place in oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Stir once in a while.
Melt cream cheese in a double boiler.
Mix in one box of powdered sugar.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Put out into buttered dish.
Cut when firm.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Separate rolls.
Place in greased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press.
Spoon meat over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes followed by Swiss and Cheddar cheese.*
Beat eggs and milk with salt and pepper.
Pour on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked onion
directions: Put flour in 1 turkey size cooking bag and shake until dusted. Clean onions and cut off ends so they will sit level.
Put butter on each onion.
Sprinkle with mint and salt to taste.
Put onions in bag.
Punch 10 to 12 holes in top side of bag.
Bake at 325° until tender.
This takes about an hour.

title: 15 minute chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in deep skillet,
add chicken and cook until browned, Remove chicken. Add soup, water, paprika, and pepper. Stir.
Heat to a boil. Stir in rice and broccoli, Place chicken back on top.
Season chicken with a little more paprika and pepper.
Cover and cook on low heat for 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: raspberry-chocolate cream
directions: Layer 1/2 of whipped topping, 1 Tbsp. syrup and 1/8 of raspberries in each of 4 dessert dishes. Repeat with remaining ingredients.

title: potato salad
directions: Put onion and vinegar in blender until fine.
Mix all together.
Sprinkle with parsley to serve.

title: sausage nuggets
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly with hands and form into balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes (watch them) or until golden brown. Drain on paper towel. After cool, they can be frozen, then reheated as needed.

title: adrienne's cole slaw
directions: *Substitute:
You can use already-prepared cabbage; comes in 8 ounce bags.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Mix dressing, sauce and juice of pineapple to make a sauce. Coat chicken in this sauce; sprinkle garlic salt on the top of each piece.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Put bread in toaster.
Put butter on the bread after it is toasted, then put sugar-cinnamon on bread.

title: cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
To prepare crust, in a medium saucepan, place 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Heat until butter is melted, stirring occasionally.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs; press evenly over bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl with a mixer, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in rest of sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time and vanilla until blended.
Spoon pie filling evenly over crust.
Pour cream cheese mixture over pie filling.
Bake just until set, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Chill until cold, about 2 hours.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: english trifle - a layered dessert
directions: Drain all liquid from canned fruit and reserve for use in cake mix as part of the water needed in box recipe.
Follow cake directions for sheet cake.
Let cool.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Crush pretzels and set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar and 1 cup of the crushed pretzels.
Pat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Let crust cool.

title: old fashioned apple crisp
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
Place sliced apples in dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
In a small bowl, mix together flour, sugar and butter.
Drop mixture over apples. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and fill jellyroll pan or pizza pan (may be too much for one pan).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool!

title: far east casserole(vegetable casserole)
directions: Cook celery in boiling water for 8 minutes, just until slightly crisp.
Mix all ingredients together and place in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.

title: water whip pie crust
directions: Mix water, shortening and milk.
Whip until creamy with a fork or mixer.
Mix flour and salt together; add to shortening.
Stir until mixed.
Roll out to fit pie pan.
Bake in hot oven, 425°, for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stain remover
directions: Put in a large bucket, using the hottest water available. Stir well.
Add stained clothes and leave overnight.
Wash as usual in washing machine.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into bite-size pieces.
Place potatoes and oil in mixing bowl and mix until potatoes are well coated. Add onion soup mix.
Mix well.
Place potatoes in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° or 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown and tender.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all together and make into a roll.
Wrap in foil (shiny side in) and refrigerate 24 hours.
Poke holes in bottom of foil and place on rack on broiler pan. Put a little water in broiler pan.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Unwrap to cool.
Slice off and eat.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and salt in 1 cup very hot water in large bowl of mixer.
Mix yeast in 3/4 cup warm water.
Mix with Crisco mixture when it cools to lukewarm.
Add beaten eggs and 5 cups flour.
Mix well and use dough hook to knead.
Add 1 cup flour slowly.
Put in large greased bowl; cover and refrigerate overnight.
About 3 hours before time to bake, roll and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter, fold and pinch edge together.
Place on greased large 14 x 17-inch pan.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen rolls.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with two strips of bacon (if you like that flavor).
Pour over all one 8 ounce can of tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add egg; beat well.
Combine milk and soda.
Combine flour and spices.
Add to cream mixture, alternating with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in apple butter and nuts.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone in small pieces. Mix all together and bake at 350° until done.

title: warm taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Spread chili, then green chilies and chopped onions, then salsa and cover with shredded cheese; warm in oven until cheese is melted.

title: apple-orange pinwheel salad
directions: Cut unpared apple into wedges.
Arrange apple wedges and orange sections in pinwheel design on salad greens.
Drizzle Honey Dressing on fruit.
Makes 2 servings.

title: banana bread "lite"
directions: Mix all wet ingredients, then mix in dry.
Spray loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: japanese fruitcake pie
directions: Mix melted butter and sugar; let cool to room temperature. Add eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and pour evenly into unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Beat cream cheese until blended.
Add powdered sugar and blend thoroughly.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of cracker crumbs.
Add pineapple on top of cream cheese mixture.
Slice bananas on top of pineapple.
Top with whipped topping.
Decorate with cherries and nuts.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain well.
Melt margarine; drizzle a couple of tablespoons of melted margarine over cracker crumbs and mix.
Add Velveeta to remaining margarine and melt together while stirring.
Pour melted cheese over broccoli in a casserole dish; mix.
Sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs over top.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix margarine and sugar; beat until creamy.
Add eggs individually.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to batter.
Stir in coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: angel delight
directions: Tear angel cakes into bite size pieces. Set aside.
Mix together cream cheese, 10x sugar and Cool Whip.
Stir in angel pieces.
Place in Tupperware container.
Pour pie filling over top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.
It can be put directly into refrigerator or canned in glass containers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat well.
Blend in the dry ingredients.
Add carrots, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until well done.

title: fudgy chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl combine flour, sugar and cocoa. Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In saucepan, melt 1 cup chips with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Pour over crust.
Top with walnuts and remaining chocolate chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: jello pies
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and pineapple juice.
Cook a few minutes, add Jello.
Mix well.
Let cool.
In a large bowl, whip ice cold Pet milk.
Add cool Jello mixture.
Line pie plates with vanilla wafers, stand them around the edges.
Pour Jello mixture into pie plates.
Put in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
Makes two pies.

title: chow mein
directions: Mix all ingredients except noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top with noodles.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: margaret's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening together until smooth.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, blending just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add milk, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Tap pan on flat surface several times to remove air bubbles from batter.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 275° and bake for 2 to 3 hours or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove and cool on wire racks.
Yields 16 servings.

title: crispy peanut butter balls(candy)
directions: Combine peanut butter, marshmallow cream and Rice Krispies (mix until well blended).
Shape into small balls and set aside.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut into strips.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat and cook, turning often, until brown.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Add peppers (cut into strips) and tomatoes (cut into strips) the last 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce; stir into meat mixture.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Put mixture in an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool and chill. Use Cool Whip on top for serving.

title: apricot salad
directions: Make jello according to directions. Mix in all ingredients. Let congeal while making sauce.

title: chicken and pimento rice
directions: Cook rice in broth, add cream of chicken soup.
Put in baking dish, garnish with pimento bits, placing boned chicken on top. Pour remaining broth over top, if any is left, and heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse the peas and drain well.
Set aside.
Peel the potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch cubes.
Set aside in cold water.
Cut carrots into 1/4-inch dice.
Set aside.
Heat oil in a kettle and add the sausage pieces.
Cook about 1 minute and add the onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring, about 1 minute.
Add the carrots.
Cook, stirring, about 2 minutes.
Drain the peas and potatoes and add them.
Add the chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and cook about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until peas have become quite liquid.
Serve hot.

title: berlin scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Set aside.
In the same skillet, cook the onion in reserved drippings until tender.
Add spinach.
Heat through.

In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish or oval 2-quart dish, combine potatoes and dry sauce mix from package. Stir in the boiling water and milk as directed on the package, omitting the margarine or butter.
Stir in bacon, spinach, onion mixture and caraway seed.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven about 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 2 to 3 minutes more or until melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 10 servings.

title: orange nut loaf
directions: Combine baking mix, sugar, eggs, orange rind and juice in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Fold in the nuts.
Pour batter into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack. Drizzle with Orange Glaze and garnish with orange zest, if desired.
Slice and serve.

title: oatmeal hermits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool, then eat.

title: simple pizza dough
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve the yeast and sugar in the lukewarm water.
Let rest until foamy, about 15 minutes.
Mix the flour and salt in a large bowl.
Add the olive oil to the yeast mixture. Make a well in the flour and add yeast mixture.
Stir to combine. Add extra flour if too sticky.
Knead on a floured board or countertop until smooth and elastic, adding flour as needed.
This should take about 5 minutes.
Pat the dough into a ball; put in large bowl and set in a warm place (near oven), covered with a clean towel.
Let rise for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: blueberry breakfast sauce
directions: In a 2-qt. saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; gradually stir in water. Add blueberries; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Serve warm or cold over French toast, pancakes, or waffles.

title: lynn's skillet barbecue chicken
directions: In large frying pan, add ingredients.
Cut up one fryer.
Set in pan and cook, uncovered, over medium heat, turning to brown evenly.
Cook until tender, about 35 minutes.
Remove chicken to a platter.
Skim off oil from sauce.
Add 1 cup water.
Stir.
Serve over chicken.

title: meat cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in enough boiling water with 2 teaspoons salt; cover and cook for about 5 minutes or until tender-crisp and drain.
Add butter, syrup, marjoram and pinch of salt.
In another bowl, mix the beef, bread crumbs, milk, eggs, salt and pepper. Butter 2-quart casserole and layer the cabbage and meat, beginning with cabbage.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until meat is done.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat
eggs
and
then
add sugar and other ingredients. Heat slowly
to
melt butter.
Cool in an unbaked pie shell at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: 5-cheese pie appetizer
directions: Place 1/2 of crescent rolls in bottom of ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan; pinch seams together.
Layer the cheeses on top in order given.

title: glazed ham
directions: Slice ham in 1/4 inch slices.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Drain juice off of pineapples and cherries in a bowl.
Add honey mustard sauce and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Place pineapple slices on top of ham; put cherries in centers of pineapples.
Pour mixture over ham.
Bake in microwave until desired tenderness, about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: enchirito casserole
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain.
Add refried beans.
Cook until heated. Warm tortillas (until soft enough to fold).
Spoon beans and hamburger mixture into middle of tortillas.
Fold bottom up and take one slice and roll over to close.
Place rolled tortillas in square casserole pan.
Pour salsa over tortillas and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches) or 2 round layer pans (8-inch or 9 x 1 1/2-inches).
Beat all ingredients in large mixing bowl on a low speed, scraping bowl constantly for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden toothpick that is inserted into the center comes out clean.
Let cake cool.
Frost the cake.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute vegetables in margarine.
Reduce heat to low.
Add process cheese spread and milk.
Stir until cheese spread is melted.
Stir in macaroni and spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook and stir pepper and onion in hot oil in saucepan until tender, but not browned.
Add corn, salsa and broth; bring to boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add cheese; fluff with fork.
Makes 8 servings.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: On the first day, marinate brisket overnight in refrigerator in liquid smoke (I like Wright's), Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion and celery salt.
On the second day, do not pour off marinade.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, brown sugar and sweet pickle juice.
Put foil over pan and bake covered at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.
