Add frozen lemonade and stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate for exactly 20 minutes (no more, no less).
Remove from refrigerator and beat in Cool Whip.
Pour into large mold or bowl.
The jello will separate into 2 layers.

title: garden patch barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender until raisins are pulverized.
Remove and place in a saucepan.
Simmer on top of stove for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.
Great for pork!

title: sausage and rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Fry sausage. When done, combine each in pot. Crumble sausage in rice. Mix well. Use tomatoes as garnish on top. Recipe serves 3; can easily be doubled.

title: apple crisp
directions: Stir ingredients until crumbly.
Cover bottom of a greased casserole with 6 large apples, sliced.
Spread crumbly mixture over top.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine; drizzle over crumbs.
Bake in a preheated oven about 40 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Cut each half into 7 pieces. Grease a Bundt pan.
Toss generous amount of chopped nuts in bottom.
Place cut dough into pan.
Sprinkle dough with cinnamon. Sprinkle 1/2 package pudding on top.
Melt butter.
Add both sugars.
Pour over dough.
Add more nuts.
Cover with towel.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy beer bread
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a large bowl, gradually adding beer and stirring just until moistened. Spoon mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Brush top with margarine.
Cool loaf in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack. Slice with electric knife.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: plum torte
directions: Note:
Blueberries, sliced peeled peaches, apples or combinations may be used on top.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a rolling boil margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, rolled oats and vanilla. Dip out with spoon or melon ball dipper.
Drop on wax paper sheet. Let cool.

title: alabama cocoa pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in small bowl; set aside. Combine the eggs, dark corn syrup, cream, melted butter and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Add the dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pan. Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes until center is firm to the touch.
Cool.
To serve, garnish with whipped cream mound and top with pecans.

title: chicken broccoli vegetable
directions: In skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon hot butter, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove chicken.
Keep warm.
In same skillet, in remaining butter cook broccoli, carrots and mushrooms 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes or until done. Serve over rice.

title: dijon pork chops
directions: Mix mustard and milk.
Dip chops to coat both sides.
Mix breadcrumbs and spices and coat chops.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine in 2 quart saucepan until melted.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in milk and broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2 quart casserole dish (10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch).
Bake uncovered 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza wheels
directions: Combine the basil and oregano with tomato sauce.
Spread sauce on toasted muffins and sprinkle on cheese.
Drizzle on oil and place muffins on cookie sheet.
Broil until cheese melts.
Top with sliced olives, chopped green peppers or chopped green onions, if desired.
Serves 3.

title: nut torte(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the egg yolks in a mixer until thick and light. Then beat in the sugar.
When it forms a ribbon, stir in the flour, salt, baking powder, orange juice (or Jamacian rum) and the chopped nuts.
Beat the egg whites until stiff. Fold them in.
Pour into two 8-inch layer cake pans which have been greased and lined with greased wax paper.
Bake for 25 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes on a wire rack.
Remove from the pans.
Before serving, put the layers together with whipped cream flavored with the grated orange rind.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cooked carrots, oil, baking powder, cinnamon and eggs in a mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Add nuts/and or raisins. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tomato relish
directions: Peel and core tomatoes.
Add all ingredients.
Cook on top of stove in heavy boiler until thick.
Stir constantly.
Can in jars. Try this on tacos.

title: seafood stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter.
Add bread crumbs and mix.
Add mushroom stems, seasonings and seafood.
Stuff caps with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add rest of ingredients, folding in chocolate chips and grated chocolate bar last.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: rhubarb ice cream
directions: In saucepan combine rhubarb, 3/4 cup sugar and water.
Cook covered for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Cool slightly.
Add lemon juice, salt and coloring.
Pour into 8-cup freezer container.
Freeze firm.
Break into chunks.
Place in chilled bowl and beat smooth with electric beater.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar beating to stiff peaks.
Fold whipping cream into rhubarb mixture along with egg mixture.
Freeze firm.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: okra and tomato gumbo
directions: Cut okra and cook with chopped onions in a little fat until tender.
Then add a pint of whole tomatoes, a little sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook until thick.
Delicious.

title: banana pudding
directions: *Can be substituted with low-cal or low-fat; still just as good.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco mix.
Press on 8-inch plate.
Spread salsa over mixture.
Chop tomatoes, onion and black olives and layer over cheese and salsa mixture.
Chill 5 to 7 hours. Surround with chips.

title: spiced orange tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
To make one cup, put spiced-orange tea mix in a cup of boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Can be iced.
Serves 40.

title: tuna, broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Boil broccoli, celery and mushrooms together until tender, then drain.
In large glass bowl, mix soup and tuna first, then add all other ingredients.
Mix well with spoon.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, then stir.
Microwave for another 3 to 4 minutes, until all is hot.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy bottomed saucepan.
Add flour and stir until well blended.
Gradually add milk and stir constantly until thick.
Add carrots and broth.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot, sprinkled with parsley.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Fold crabmeat and 3/4 cup of cheese into mixture.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese-chive biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt with fork.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in cheese and chives.
Mix and turn onto lightly floured board.
Roll and cut in small size biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Brush with melted butter before or after baking.

title: broccoli
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add broccoli and cook until tender. Add soup, cheese, Accent, mushrooms and 3/4 c. almonds.
Pour into casserole then sprinkle reserved almonds and bread crumbs on top. Bake at 325 degrees until bubbly.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Brown meat.
Mix garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce. Add to meat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Chop onions and tops; mix with cream cheese and sour cream.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Layer noodles in lightly greased casserole dish with onion, cheese and sour cream mix and meat sauce. Repeat.
Add grated cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion together.
Drain.
Cook macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Mix hamburg, onion, soup, mushrooms and milk into macaroni.
Bake in a large casserole dish for 20 minutes, or until heated through, in a 375° oven.
No need to grease casserole dish.

title: chicken and biscuits(serves 6)
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters.
Arrange biscuit on chicken mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden.

title: creamy tuna deluxe
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package except use 3/4 cup of milk.
Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add to dinner with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate and butter.
In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
In another bowl, beat 2 eggs, 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and 3/4 cup sugar with electric mixer until thick.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Put cloves and cinnamon in cloth bag.
Drop into hot water, sugar and juices.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add tea bags (number depends on desired strength).
Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Store in refrigerator and reheat as needed.
Never boil.

title: peach delight
directions: Pour peaches with juice into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over it.
Add nuts and slice oleo and put it over top of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch square pan at 350° until cake pulls away from sides of pan or test with toothpick.

title: egg-spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach and put in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan. Put mushrooms on top of spinach and then crumble croutons and sprinkle on top of mushrooms. Beat eggs and spices and pour over top. Pour milk over top and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: white trash
directions: Melt chocolate; stir in peanut butter and peanuts. Mix with Crispix in large bowl until well coated. In a Ziploc bag, add cereal to confectioners sugar; coat well.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer as in order listed.
Can be made up the night before. Add dressing just before serving and mix well.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage with water in covered frying pan until tender, approximately 20 minutes.
Remove sausage and cook green pepper and onion for 5 minutes, then add the condensed tomato soup and heat through.
Combine sauce with macaroni and mix well.
Place in casserole with sausage arranged on top.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for approximately 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and broccoli with lemon butter
directions: Thaw shrimp; pat dry on paper towels.
In a 10-inch skillet heat half of the butter or margarine over medium-high heat.
Add broccoli and celery.
Cook for 3 or 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring often.
Remove from the skillet.
Keep warm.
In the same skillet heat remaining butter or margarine over medium heat.
Add shrimp; cook about 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink, stirring often.
Return vegetable mixture to the skillet.
Stir in lemon juice and sesame seed.
Can be served over rice, if desired.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water; cool.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Beat butter until soft in large bowl.
Add brown sugar and eggs; beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Beat in vanilla and cooled melted chocolate.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, beating well with a wooden spoon after each addition until batter is smooth.
Stir in boiling water.
Pour at once into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix together well.
Chill several hours.
Serve with assorted raw vegetables (carrots, celery, green onions, broccoli, cucumbers, cherry tomatoes, cauliflower, or whatever your favorite veggie is).

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix and drop in hot oil by spoonfuls.
Cook until brown.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken and rice - spanish)
directions: Rub chicken with oregano mixture.
Brown chicken in lard. Reduce heat to moderate fire and add onions and green pepper; cook for 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and olives and cook for 10 minutes more.
Pour 2 cups of rice into 3 cups of boiling water; cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and sauces to rice and cook at moderate flame 15 minutes.
Cover pot and cook on low for another 15 to 20 minutes.
While cooking, turn rice from bottom to top with large spoon, not too often.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Spray baking sheet with cooking spray.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Grease skillet and get hot; pour into skillet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients (flours, sugar or honey, baking powder and salt).
Use 1 cup dry mix with egg, milk and melted butter.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Let cream cheese soften.

title: snow punch(garnish each serving with flaked coconut)
directions: Advance preparation:
Pour lemon juice into blender container. Slice bananas into container.
Cover; blend until pureed.
Combine banana mixture, cream and sugar; chill.

title: broccoli with peppers
directions: In a heavy skillet (12-inch), heat olive oil over moderate heat one minute.
Add onion, garlic, water, broccoli, red pepper, oregano and red pepper flakes.
Cook, stirring, 2 minutes.
Cover skillet; reduce heat to low and cook 6 to 8 minutes longer, stirring often, until broccoli is tender, but still crisp.

title: broccoli cheddar cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray-grease muffin tins and press biscuits in, one at a time, stretching out into it.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in a bowl and spoon equal amounts into biscuit-lined muffin tin.
Can put water in muffin tins not being used.
Can eat hot or cold after being cooked in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Contains 166 calories per serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
If beans are very dry, add a little water.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Put meat in roaster - add everything.
Cover and roast at 350° 40 minutes to the pound - do not overcook.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add alternately sifted dry ingredients and milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Add vanilla and lemon.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat well.
Place in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon salad evenly into 8 custard cups; cover and freeze 8 hours, or until firm.
Before serving, place in refrigerator for 1 hour; garnish with pineapple chunks.
Serve chilled.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit slush punch
directions: In a large container, combine the first four ingredients. Stir until the sugar is dissolved.
Pour into containers and freeze.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter until mixture is fine crumbs.
Mix egg, milk and vanilla; stir into flour mixture.
Fold in frozen blueberries.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: lauren's favorite dinner
directions: Heat olive oil; add onions until semi-translucent.
Add beef. When beef is browned, add a jar of brown gravy and marinara.
Mix thoroughly while still heating.
Turn down to a simmer; add cream and white wine.
Add all to pasta and pour into a baking pan.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top; add seasonings.
Put in oven at 350° and bake for half an hour or until bubbly.
Enjoy!

title: hobo dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt, pepper, corn, and tomatoes; simmer a few minutes. Boil noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Make alternate layers of noodles, meat, and cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: peach yogurt salad
directions: Mix ingredients together. Refrigerate.

title: ripe olive rice
directions: Cook crumbled sausage until lightly browned.
Add onion and garlic; continue to cook until onion is tender.
Stir in rice. Add broth, tomatoes, mushrooms, olives, oregano, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and cook slowly for 20 minutes, if raw rice is used.
(Leftover, cooked rice may be used).
Heat thoroughly over low heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Combine spinach and artichokes.
Combine cream cheese and next three ingredients.
Stir into spinach mixture.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes and uncovered for an additional 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix and roll in balls, then roll in sugar.
Bake at 350°.

title: shrimp bites
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cheese together.
Place shrimp on a cracker, dot with mayonnaise mixture and broil until golden.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Let Cool Whip warm to room temperature.
Melt chocolate chips and mix with Cool Whip; pour into graham cracker crust.
Garnish with chocolate shavings if desired.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons of juice drained from pineapple with mayonnaise, mustard, curry powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cut chicken into small slivers and mix with remaining ingredients. Add flavored mayonnaise and blend well.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: 6 layer cookie
directions: Grease sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter and pour into pan.
Add the crushed graham crackers.
Pour over butter.
Pour milk over crackers.
Spread chips over milk, then spread coconut over chips and last sprinkle nuts over chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If baking in a glass pan, bake at 325° for the same amount of time.
Bars should be lightly browned. Chill in pan for at least 4 hours. Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a double boiler, mix flour, cocoa and sugar together.
Add 1/3 cup milk.
Mix together well. Add yolks, blending well.
Add remaining milk and vanilla.
Cook (stirring to keep from scorching) over medium heat until thickened.
Pour into baked deep dish pie shell.

title: pumpkin cheesecake with praline sauce
directions: Use butter to grease 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine other ingredients and press into bottom and up sides of pan. Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix spices, baking powder and sugar.
Put butter in hot potatoes.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 45 minutes longer.
This makes 2 pies.

title: iowa stuffing
directions: Bake at 450° for 5 hours or until the popcorn blows the end out of the turkey.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers and take out seeds.
Put peppers in cold water and bring to a boil.
Boil approximately 3 minutes or until they just start to soften.
Drain good.
Salt and pepper inside of peppers.
Put peppers in baking dish and fill with the following:

title: hoke cakes
directions: Combine
the ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
In large skillet, pour in oil.
When hot, spoon in batter to
make pancake like cakes.
Brown on both sides.
(After oil gets hot, reduce heat to medium-low.)

title: chess pie
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg in bowl.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, extract, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
After mixing well, pour over other ingredients in pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, or until brown to your taste.

title: pralines
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large, heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until sugar dissolves. Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan. Uncover and cook to soft-ball stage (234°), stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla. Beat with wooden spoon just until mixture begins to thicken. Working rapidly, drop by tablespoons onto greased wax paper. Let stand until firm. Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: fruity muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Combine oats, flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Combine remaining ingredients and mix with dry ingredients just until moistened.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix the flour, salt, sugar and baking powder; cut in butter until particles are small pea-size.
Put baking soda in egg yolks and sour cream.
Stir.
Mix into dry ingredients.
Roll out to fit 9 x 12-inch cake pan, including sides.
Place dough in pan (leave 1/4 for top).
Add pie filling.
Make lattice top with remaining dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fruit salad (for weight watchers)
directions: Drain fruit, save juices!!!
Use juice in place of milk as directed on pudding box.
Pour pudding mixture over fruits, chill and
serve.
Most
any type fruits can be used and this stores well in refrigerator.

title: bean and pea salad
directions: Mix and set aside.

title: cranberry-banana nut bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
In another bowl, combine eggs, sugar, mashed cranberries, mashed banana and cooking oil.
Add this mixture to the flour mixture. Stir well.
Add nuts and stir.

title: delicious chocolate icing
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together and put in saucepan.
Add oleo, canned milk and the vanilla.
Mix real well and bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute after it comes to full boil. After boiling 1 minute, beat as it cools.
Very good icing and easy to make.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in unsalted water for 10 to 15 minutes.
In another pan, slowly saute oleo and onion until onion is tender. Add the soup and cheese; heat until cheese is melted.
Pour boiling water over the rice; cover and set aside.
When rice is tender, add to the cheese mixture.
Pour drained vegetables and cheese mixture into casserole dish.
Top with buttered crumbs, French fried onions or potato chip crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (or less).

title: marinated tereyaki chicken wings
directions: Clean chicken. Mix ingredients and pour over chicken in a 13 by 9 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning occasionally.

title: southern-style sausage stuffing
directions: Combine sausage, celery and onion in large skillet.
Saute mixture over medium heat until sausage is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain well.
Pour sausage mixture into large bowl. Add cornbread and remaining ingredients in order listed.
Blend well.
Stuff mixture into bird.
Roast according to standard roasting directions.
Mixture may also be baked in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Makes 12 cups stuffing.

title: salmon puff
directions: Combine all ingredients
and
bake in greased casserole, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat crepes
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add margarine.
Place over medium-high heat until margarine melts.
Add mushrooms, green onions and 1 teaspoon thyme; saute 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Reduce heat to low; stir in flour. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in crabmeat and next 5 ingredients.

title: hot cheddar dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nut chewies
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and butter until creamy.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Add egg mixture.
Mix at low until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Mixture will be stiff.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Mix everything together and put in a casserole dish.
Cook at 350° until bubbly through and through. Put cheese on top.
You can put some cheese in the mixture too before cooking it.
Serve with flour tortillas and salad.

title: shrimp fritters
directions: Bring water to a boil with butter, add flour all at once, stirring well until mixture leaves the side of saucepan.
Remove from heat and add well beaten eggs, stir until smooth and thick. Stir in shrimp and cheese.
Drop by small spoonfuls into shallow hot fat.
Brown on both sides.
Serves 6.
May double recipe.

title: cabbage-beef casserole
directions: Chop cabbage.
Place in greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onions, stir in rice.
Pour over cabbage.
Mix soup and water. Pour over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add more water if needed.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients; add to first mixture alternately with zucchini.
Stir in raisins, walnuts and vanilla.
Bake in 2 greased and lightly floured loaf pans at 350° on lowest baking rack for about 55 minutes.

title: egg casserole supreme
directions: This is a yummy luncheon or appetizer recipe.
Be sure to use mild green chilies, not the hot ones.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Stir first 6 ingredients.
Then add remaining ingredients.

title: picante sauce
directions: In a large pot, combine all ingredients.
Cook down for 3 1/2 hours.
Pour into clean jars; seal and hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: toby soup
directions: Saute the onion, celery and garlic in oleo.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add 1 cup precooked rice the last 15 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt or to taste. Add McKay's seasoning.
Before serving, add milk.
Serve with a scoop of cottage cheese in soup bowl.

title: amish chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove from broth and cut into small pieces.
Add celery, onions, salt, pepper and garlic to broth. Cook until tender.
Add chicken and corn and cook about 1/2 hour. Thicken a little with flour and water.
Very good.

title: heavenly stew
directions: Mix together in crock-pot on high heat 5 to 7 hours.
If more soup needed, add another can tomato soup and another 1/2 can water.

title: cream cherry frosting
directions: Sprinkle gelatin into cherry juice
to soften.
Heat in microwave for 10 to 15 seconds.
Cool
a
minute or two.
Then whip mixture into topping with wire
whip.
Frost
cake, garnishing with sliced almonds.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry minute pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Pour boiling water over gelatin.
Stir and dissolve.
Add frozen strawberries; stir to break berries apart. When mixture is partially set, pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until set.
If desired, serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar. Roll into balls and refrigerate.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together; dip balls.
Cool on wax paper.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Add the first mixture, without stirring.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ho ho bars
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into a 10 x 15-inch greased pan.
Bake 12 - 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Let cool.
Combine sugar, margarine, shortening, milk, vanilla, salt. Beat till fluffy, 10 - 15 minutes.
You must use an electric mixer. Spread over cooled cake.
Melt frosting in microwave for 20-25 seconds to soften.
Spread over cream layer.

title: shortbread
directions: Blend together all the ingredients; form in 2 x 10-inch rolls. Beat egg white; dip rolls in or brush on.
Then roll the rolls in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Refrigerate for better handling. Cut 1/4-inch slices and bake on a greased cookie sheet until brown.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix well and knead to make a roll.
Chill overnight.
Slice and bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Spread the 2 1/2 cups crushed vanilla wafers in the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Beat the egg, powdered sugar and oleo; spread over crumbs.
Spread the raspberries.
Spread the Cool Whip. Sprinkle 1/2 cup crushed wafers on top.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: deer summer sausage
directions: Day 1:
Mix all ingredients by hand.
Put in large airtight container.
Refrigerate.

title: spanish meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and form into a loaf.
Place in Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Microwave chicken for 10 minutes until chicken is white, let cool.
Cut into tiny pieces.
Roll chicken up in crescent rolls. Put soup in bottom of casserole dish.
Lay chicken rolls on soup. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Turn rolls after 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover.
Let cheese melt and serve.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Add the eggs, oil and pineapple.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into a sheet cake pan that has been oiled and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool Whip can be used for frosting or use the following frosting.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour and salt and add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: chicken breasts bridget
directions: Pound chicken breasts thin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat 1 teaspoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to warm platter.
Add green onions, lemon juice, wine, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, stirring constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter and oil. Pour sauce over chicken and serve immediately.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream
butter
or
shortening and brown sugar.	Add eggs and molasses.
Sift
together flour, cinnamon and ginger.
Add flour mixture
and milk alternately. When well mixed, add soda dissolved in
small	amount of hot water.
Stir well.
Bake in moderate oven
until
knife	comes
out clean.
Serve with hot lemon sauce or whipped cream.

title: potato cakes with cheese
directions: Roll potatoes into flat sheet.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Fold over and cut into small squares.
Fry until light brown in butter.

title: low fat biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl; add oil and milk. Knead dough until mixed. Pat down dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut biscuits. Bake on a cookie sheet at 450° until brown.

title: best yet pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and the flavoring.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Add batter. Place in cold oven.
Set temperature at 300° and bake for 3 hours 35 minutes.
Secret for this delicious cake is all ingredients are to be out of the refrigerator for 2 hours before preparing.

title: mushrooms on toast
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add mushrooms and flour; toss to coat.
Stir in water, bouillon cube, salt, basil and hot pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve piping hot on toast.

title: italian potato wedges
directions: Slice potatoes into wedge shaped slices, leaving skins on. Put into baking pan.
Sprinkle with steak and Italian seasonings. Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Turn after 25 minutes. (A great alternative to French fries.)

title: christmas tree cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg and lemon juice; mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Divide dough in half; wrap each portion in plastic wrap and chill at least 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.
Roll each portion to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut with a 5-inch tree shaped cookie cutter; place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer to wire rack to cool. Spread green frosting on cookies; let dry.
Yield:
2 dozen, 5-inch cookies.

title: buttermilk scones
directions: Soften the yeast in warm water.
Pour warm buttermilk into a large warm bowl.
Add the sugar, eggs, oil, salt, baking powder and baking soda; mix well.
Add the softened yeast and mix.
Add 4 cups of flour and beat until smooth.
Add the remaining 4 cups of flour to make dough soft.
Cover; let the dough rise in a warm place about 1 hour or until double in bulk.
Punch the dough down to its original size.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: mommom's macaroni and cheese
directions: In a saucepan, melt oleo over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat about 10 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the cheese until melted.
Turn macaroni into greased 2-quart casserole. Pour cheese mixture over macaroni; mix well. Mix remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli pepperoni bread
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Coat pan with olive oil.
Return drained broccoli to pan and add other ingredients.
Cook a few minutes until cheese melts.
Cool.
Stretch and roll dough 16 x 5 inches.
Spread mixture to 1/2 inch of edge.
Fold over and pinch edges.
Put seam on bottom.
Put on greased pan.
Put 1-inch slit on top.
Brush top with egg and water (beat egg with 1 teaspoon water).
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: phill henke and glen parker's salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients
except Ro-Tel tomatoes. Blend on lowest setting of blender.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: sherry wine cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and pierce holes in cake with large fork or skewer and pour mixture of last 3 ingredients over cake.
Return to oven for another 10 minutes.
Use a 10-inch greased tube pan.

title: sauterne scallop bake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir scallops and mushrooms into liquid mixture; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove scallops and mushrooms from saucepan, reserving liquid in pan; set scallops and mushrooms aside.
Bring liquid to a boil and cook, uncovered, 10 minutes or until liquid is reduced to 1/2 cup.

title: slow cooker pot roast
directions: Wash the roast and place it in a slow cooker.
Cover with onion soup mix and stewed tomatoes.
Cook on high for one hour, then turn to low setting and cook for six hours or until tender. Thicken the gravy with flour or cornstarch, if preferred.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat well.
Add flour and pecans.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape dough into small finger-like rolls.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: country chicken stew
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
In hot drippings, cook onion and oregano until tender.
Stir in soup, water, potatoes and carrots. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans; cover. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in crumbled bacon, chicken and parsley. Heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: church salad
directions: Thaw the broccoli and cauliflower; layer in large Pyrex dish. Add layer
of
chopped
onions
and green pepper.
Pour over this the
mayonnaise,
covering	completely.
Over
this place layer of chopped lettuce, then add the cheese.
Over the cheese, sprinkle 1 jar of Bac*Os.
Crumbled, crisp bacon could be
used. Refrigerate
several
hours
or
overnight	before serving.
Makes a very large salad.

title: chicken in crumb basket
directions: Combine bread crumbs with onion, seasoning and butter.
Line large casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan with crumb mixture.
Press in place; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Melt butter; blend in flour. Add milk, chicken broth and seasoning.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add peas and chicken.
Serves 6.

title: odessa's red beans and rice
directions: Cook slowly for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all together before combining with shredded cabbage for cole slaw.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and pat dry; prick each potato several times with a fork.
Arrange potatoes end to end and 1 inch apart in a circle on paper towels in microwave oven.
Microwave on High for 12 to 14 minutes, turning and rearranging potatoes after 6 minutes.
Let potatoes stand for 5 minutes.

title: pizza pockets
directions: Put soft tortilla shells on a pan.
Spread sauce on it.
Just a little. Then sprinkle both cheeses on the sauce.
Add pepperoni on cheese.
Cook until cheese melts at 375°.

title: easy supper
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, salt and pepper.
Place in bottom of casserole.
Cover with drained corn.
Cover with leftover mashed potatoes.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Warm in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add melted chocolate.
Beat yolks; add water and extract and blend.
Gradually add yolk mixture to chocolate mixture; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk, blending well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Turn into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans or one greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake layers or loaf in moderate oven, 350°, for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in pan.
Then add the remaining dry ingredients.
Pour over all 1 1/2 cups of hot water.
Bake at 350° until done, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lobster casserole
directions: Put all together in casserole with grated cheese on top and croutons on the very top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve on or with rice or wide noodles.
